Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide chips (no need to peel).

Zest and halve the @lemon{½}.

Finely chop the @flat leaf parsley{1%bunch}(chopped, stalks and all). Pick the @mint{1%bunch}(leaves picked) leaves from their stalks and roughly chop (discard the stalks).

Finely chop the @capers{30%grams}.

== Crushed Peas ==

Put the @peas{120%grams} in a #medium bowl{} and add a drizzle of @olive oil{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Roughly mash with a #potato masher{} or fork until broken up and crushed.

Stir through the chopped mint and lemon zest, then set aside.

== Chips ==

Pop the chips onto a #large baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

== Tartare Sauce ==

Meanwhile, put the capers, parsley and @mayonnaise{64%grams} in a #small bowl{}. Add a squeeze of lemon juice and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Mix together, then set your tartare sauce aside.

== Fish Fingers ==

Cut each @basa fillets{2} into 3 equal-sized 'fingers'.

Crack the @egg{1} (see pantry for amount) into a medium bowl and whisk. Put the @breadcrumbs{50%grams} into another bowl, season with the @salt{¼%tsp} (see pantry for amount) and @pepper{}.

Season the fish, then dip each fish finger into the egg and then the breadcrumbs, ensuring it's completely coated. Transfer to a clean #plate{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw fish.

Pop a #large frying pan{} on high heat and add enough @oil{} to coat the bottom of the pan.

> TIP: You want the oil to be hot so the fish fries properly - heat for 2-3 mins before you add the fish.

Once hot, lay the fish fingers in the pan and cook until crispy and golden, ~{6-8%minutes}. Turn every couple of mins.

> IMPORTANT: The fish is cooked when opaque in the middle.

Once cooked, transfer to a plate lined with #kitchen paper{}.

== Assembly ==

Just before serving, pop the @burger buns{2} into the oven to warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

When everything's ready, spoon the crushed peas over the bun bases and spread the tartare sauce over the lids. Top the bases with the fish fingers, then sandwich shut with the bun lids.

Serve your ultimate fish finger sarnie with any remaining crushed peas, the chips and @baby leaf mix{50%grams} alongside.

Add a squeeze of @lemon juice{} and a drizzle of @olive oil{} over the salad to finish.

Enjoy!